#Lambda (Serverless Compute)

Basic Questions:

âœ… What is AWS Lambda?
â— A serverless compute service that runs code in response to events.

âœ… How does AWS Lambda work?
â— Triggered by AWS services (e.g., S3, API Gateway, CloudWatch).
â— Runs code in a fully managed environment.

âœ… What are some common Lambda use cases?
â— File processing (S3 events)
â— API backends (API Gateway + Lambda)
â— Real-time stream processing (Kinesis, DynamoDB Streams)

Advanced Questions:

âœ… How do you secure an AWS Lambda function?
â— Attach IAM Roles with least privilege access.
â— Use VPC for private execution.
â— Enable Lambda function URL authentication if exposed externally.

âœ… How does Lambda scale?
â— Automatically scales with incoming requests.
â— Concurrency limit can be configured.

âœ… How can you reduce cold start issues in Lambda?
â— Use Provisioned Concurrency.
â— Use smaller function sizes.
â— Choose warm-up strategies (e.g., scheduled invocations).

Advanced Questions:

Lambda (Serverless Compute)

âœ… How does AWS Lambda scale under heavy load?
â— Lambda scales by launching multiple concurrent executions.
â— AWS provides soft and hard concurrency limits.
â— Use Provisioned Concurrency to minimize cold starts.

âœ… What are the best practices to optimize AWS Lambda performance?
â— Minimize cold starts by using smaller function sizes.
â— Use AWS SDK v3 to reduce package size.
â— Use ARM-based Lambda (Graviton2) for better performance.
â— Use async processing with SQS & SNS instead of waiting for responses.

âœ… How can you securely run AWS Lambda inside a VPC?
â— Attach the Lambda function to a VPC with private subnets.
â— Use a NAT Gateway to allow outbound internet access.
â— Enable VPC endpoints for AWS services (e.g., S3, DynamoDB).

âœ… How do you troubleshoot AWS Lambda failures?
â— Check CloudWatch Logs for execution logs.
â— Use AWS X-Ray for distributed tracing.
â— Enable DLQs (Dead Letter Queues) for handling failed event-driven Lambdas.

AWS Lambda - Deep Dive:

Key Concepts

â— Serverless compute that automatically scales.
â— Supports multiple triggers: S3 events, API Gateway, DynamoDB Streams, SQS,
SNS, EventBridge.

Best Practices:

âœ… Reduce Cold Starts
â— Use Provisioned Concurrency to keep functions warm.
â— Minimize function size and dependencies (use Lambda Layers).
â— Use ARM-based Lambda (Graviton2) for faster startup.

âœ… Optimize Execution Time
â— Streamline function execution by reducing API calls and batch processing data.
â— Use async processing (SNS/SQS) instead of synchronous requests.

âœ… Secure Lambda Functions
â— Use IAM Role with least privileges to restrict access.
â— Run in a VPC if accessing private resources.
â— Enable AWS X-Ray for tracing requests.

Architecture Design:

Event-Driven Serverless Architecture

ğŸ”¹ API Gateway + Lambda + DynamoDB: Serverless API backend.
ğŸ”¹ S3 + Lambda + Step Functions: Automated data processing pipeline.
ğŸ”¹ Kinesis Streams + Lambda: Real-time event processing.

