EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)

Basic Questions:

âœ… What is AWS EC2?
â— Virtual machine service on AWS.

âœ… What are different EC2 instance types?
â— Compute Optimized (C-series) â†’ High CPU workloads.
â— Memory Optimized (R-series) â†’ High RAM (e.g., databases).
â— Storage Optimized (I-series) â†’ High-speed storage (e.g., analytics).
â— General Purpose (T-series) â†’ Balanced workloads.

âœ… What is an EC2 Security Group?
â— A firewall controlling inbound/outbound traffic.

Advanced Questions:

âœ… What are EC2 Spot, Reserved, and On-Demand instances?
â— Spot â†’ Cheap, interruptible.
â— Reserved â†’ Long-term commitment (1-3 years).
â— On-Demand â†’ Pay-as-you-go.

âœ… How do you scale EC2 instances automatically?
â— Use Auto Scaling Groups (ASG) with policies.

âœ… What is an Elastic IP, and when do you use it?
â— A static IP assigned to an instance, useful for high availability setups

Advanced Questions:
EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)

âœ… How do you troubleshoot high CPU utilization on an EC2 instance?
â— Check CloudWatch CPU Utilization metrics.
â— Use top or htop inside the instance for real-time monitoring.
â— Identify processes using high CPU with AWS Systems Manager Run Command.
â— Scale up the instance type (e.g., from t3.medium â†’ c5.large).
â— Enable Auto Scaling for dynamic resource allocation.

âœ… How do you configure EC2 Auto Scaling for high availability?
â— Use multiple Availability Zones (AZs).
â— Configure Auto Scaling Group (ASG) policies (CPU-based, schedule-based).
â— Attach an Elastic Load Balancer (ELB) for traffic distribution.
â— Use EC2 Spot Instances for cost-optimized scaling.

âœ… What are the security best practices for EC2 instances?
â— Apply IAM Roles instead of storing credentials inside EC2.
â— Restrict SSH access using Security Groups and bastion hosts.
â— Enable EC2 Instance Connect instead of password-based SSH.
â— Encrypt EBS volumes using AWS KMS.
â— Regularly patch instances using AWS Systems Manager Patch Manager.

EC2 - Deep Dive:

Key Concepts:

â— Instance Types: Compute Optimized (C5), Memory Optimized (R5), General
Purpose (T3), Storage Optimized (I3).
â— Pricing Models: On-Demand, Reserved, Spot Instances, Savings Plans.

Best Practices:

âœ… Auto Scaling & High Availability
â— Deploy instances in multiple AZs using Auto Scaling Groups (ASG).
â— Use Elastic Load Balancer (ALB, NLB) for traffic distribution.

âœ… Security & Monitoring
â— Enable AWS Inspector to scan EC2 instances for vulnerabilities.
â— Use EC2 Instance Connect for SSH instead of public IPs.
â— Store logs in CloudWatch Logs for auditing.

Architecture Design:

Highly Available EC2-Based Web Application

ğŸ”¹ Auto Scaling Group across multiple AZs.
ğŸ”¹ ALB for load balancing with HTTPS termination.
ğŸ”¹ RDS Multi-AZ for database redundancy.
ğŸ”¹ CloudFront + WAF for DDoS protection.

