CloudWatch (Monitoring & Logging)

Basic Questions:

âœ… What is AWS CloudWatch?
â— A monitoring service for AWS resources and applications.

âœ… What are CloudWatch Alarms?
â— Alerting mechanism based on metrics.

âœ… What are CloudWatch Logs?
â— Stores log data from AWS services and custom applications.

Advanced Questions:

âœ… How do you monitor EC2 with CloudWatch?
â— Use EC2 Detailed Monitoring for 1-minute metrics.
â— Enable CloudWatch Logs Agent to collect logs.

âœ… Whatâ€™s the difference between CloudWatch and CloudTrail?
â— CloudWatch â†’ Monitors performance (metrics, logs, alarms).
â— CloudTrail â†’ Logs API calls for security/audit.

Advanced Questions:

CloudWatch (Monitoring & Logging)

âœ… How do you monitor and troubleshoot high memory usage in an EC2 instance
using CloudWatch?
â— Enable CloudWatch Agent to collect memory usage metrics.
â— Use CloudWatch Alarms to trigger alerts when memory exceeds a threshold.
â— Enable AWS Lambda auto-remediation (e.g., restart instance on high memory).

âœ… Whatâ€™s the difference between CloudWatch Logs, Metrics, and Events?
â— CloudWatch Logs â†’ Stores log data from applications and AWS services.
â— CloudWatch Metrics â†’ Stores numerical time-series data (e.g., CPU usage).
â— CloudWatch Events (EventBridge) â†’ Triggers actions based on AWS events.

âœ… How do you monitor Lambda execution time using CloudWatch?
â— Check Duration metric in CloudWatch Metrics.
â— Set up a CloudWatch Alarm if execution time exceeds a threshold.
â— Enable AWS X-Ray to analyze execution bottlenecks.

CloudWatch - Deep Dive:

Key Concepts

â— CloudWatch Metrics: CPU, Memory, Network, Disk Usage.
â— CloudWatch Logs: Centralized logging for EC2, Lambda, ECS, API Gateway.
â— CloudWatch Alarms: Automated alerts based on thresholds.

Best Practices:

âœ… Monitor Key Performance Indicators
â— Set up Custom Metrics (e.g., application errors, request latency).
â— Use CloudWatch Logs Insights for querying logs.

âœ… Automate Incident Response
â— Use CloudWatch Alarms + SNS for real-time notifications.
â— Trigger AWS Lambda for auto-remediation (e.g., restart an instance).

