ECS (Elastic Container Service)

Basic Questions:

âœ… What is AWS ECS?
â— A managed container orchestration service.

âœ… What are the key components of ECS?
â— Cluster â†’ Logical grouping of container instances.
â— Task Definition â†’ Defines container settings.
â— Service â†’ Manages running tasks.

âœ… What is the difference between Fargate and EC2 launch types in ECS?
â— Fargate â†’ Serverless, AWS manages infrastructure.
â— EC2 â†’ You manage EC2 instances.

Advanced Questions:

âœ… How do you scale ECS containers?
â— Use Service Auto Scaling.
â— Application Load Balancer (ALB) can distribute traffic.

âœ… How does ECS integrate with IAM?
â— Uses IAM Task Roles for permissions.

Advanced Questions:

ECS (Elastic Container Service)

âœ… How does ECS manage networking for containers?
â— Uses AWS VPC Networking Mode (awsvpc) for ENI-based networking.
â— Supports bridge mode and host mode for EC2-based tasks.
â— Load balances traffic using ALB + Target Groups.

âœ… How do you configure ECS service discovery?
â— Use AWS Cloud Map for dynamic service discovery.
â— Integrate with Route 53 DNS-based discovery.

âœ… How do you implement rolling updates in ECS?
â— Define minimum and maximum healthy percent for tasks.
â— Use ECS Service Auto Scaling to manage traffic shift.
â— Update tasks with blue/green deployments using AWS CodeDeploy.

ECS (Elastic Container Service) - Deep-Dive:

Key Concepts:

â— Launch Types: EC2-backed or Fargate (serverless).
â— Service Discovery: Uses AWS Cloud Map for automatic DNS resolution.

Best Practices:

âœ… Use Fargate for Serverless Containers
â— No need to manage EC2 instances; scales automatically.

âœ… Secure ECS Containers
â— Use IAM Task Roles for least privilege access.
â— Scan images using Amazon Inspector for vulnerabilities.

