EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)

Basic Questions:

âœ… What is AWS EKS?
â— A managed Kubernetes service on AWS.

âœ… How is EKS different from ECS?
â— EKS â†’ Uses Kubernetes, more flexibility.
â— ECS â†’ AWS-native, simpler to manage.

âœ… What components does EKS manage?
â— The Kubernetes Control Plane (you manage worker nodes).

Advanced Questions:

âœ… How do you secure an EKS cluster?
â— Use IAM Roles for Service Accounts (IRSA).
â— Enable RBAC (Role-Based Access Control).
â— Use private networking for worker nodes.

âœ… How does EKS handle scaling?
â— Cluster Autoscaler (scales worker nodes).
â— Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) (scales pods based on CPU/memory).

Advanced Questions:

EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)

âœ… How does EKS authenticate users and control access?
â— Uses IAM Roles for Service Accounts (IRSA) for pod-level permissions.
â— Integrates with RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) for Kubernetes permissions.
â— Uses AWS Authenticator to map IAM users to Kubernetes roles.

âœ… How do you implement auto-scaling in AWS EKS?
â— Cluster Autoscaler â†’ Adds/removes worker nodes based on demand.
â— Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) â†’ Scales pods based on CPU/memory.
â— Vertical Pod Autoscaler (VPA) â†’ Adjusts pod resources dynamically.

âœ… How do you optimize EKS cluster costs?
â— Use EC2 Spot Instances for worker nodes.
â— Right-size nodes using AWS Compute Optimizer.
â— Enable Karpenter for automatic node scaling.

âœ… How do you secure an EKS cluster running in a VPC?
â— Restrict public access to the EKS API server.
â— Use Network Policies to restrict pod-to-pod communication.
â— Enable AWS WAF and Shield for DDoS protection.

EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service) -Deep Dive:

Key Concepts:

â— Managed Kubernetes service that abstracts control plane management.
â— Supports autoscaling: Cluster Autoscaler, Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA).

Best Practices:

âœ… Optimize Cost with Spot Instances
â— Use Karpenter for automatic node scaling.

âœ… Secure Kubernetes Clusters
â— Enable IAM for Service Accounts (IRSA) to restrict pod-level access.
â— Use AWS PrivateLink to keep EKS API server private.
